																		Harassment Policy
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adminbright" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(224440); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=224440&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610251601" alt="AdminBright" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=224440)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/adminbright" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(224440); return false;" >AdminBright</a></span> <span class="odate time_1372311471 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Jun 2013 05:37</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1805042">
									

<p>Hey there kids, your friendly neighborhood Admin here with something I feel needs to be said. It's coming from me, so the words may nto be perfect, but look at the intention, and we should be fine.</p>
<p>You see, we have a very simple policy when it comes to Harassment on the wiki:</p>
<p>It's not allowed. Period. At all.</p>
<p>If you believe someone is harassing you, if you are being threatened, blackmailed, or in any way being hurt by another member of the site, tell staff about it. We do not want abusers of any kind on this site, and will do our best to remove ANY harassers from anything the site can do. Personally, I am online six-14 hours a day, and check my site PMs anywhere from 2 to 15 times a day. While I am blunt and short spoken, my inbox is ALWAYS open to anyone who wants to PM me. Ideally, I would prefer a problem of this magnitude be taken straight to the Admins, but if you have someone you trust more on Staff, go them. They'll make sure everything gets done right.</p>
<p>There will be no victim blaming or shaming on this site, and anyone who reports on issues will be kept anonymous unless they are okay with otherwise. All reports will be treated seriously.</p>
<p>The SCP Foundation is something we on the Staff do for fun. No one pays us to do this, we just really like it. We want it to be a safe place for ALL our members, and hope you'll help us keep it that way.</p>
<p>If I have to break out my panel on 'How not to be a creeper,' I will.</p>
<p>(This post stickied and posted on both announcements and general forums, to ensure the most amount of viewing.)</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>Admin, SCP Wiki</p>

				</div>
					
					
